word,' b'every point of logic that they used. every moment of shared communication' b'speaks against their total skepticism. their very insistence of trying to make' b'sense is eloquent testimony to assumptions that are powerful though silent.' b'' b'that is to say, that complete skepticism is impossible and limited skepticism' b'is arbitrary. next time you\'re in a room of skeptics, yell out "look, your fly' b'is undone!" each person chooses what he is skeptical about and what he' b'believes without skepticism. to stress this is to belabor the obvious, but it' b'underlines the point that no one can know exhaustively how he knows what he' b'knows. pure objectivism is a myth and complete skepticism an impossiblity.' b'the answer to this impasse lies in a 3rd way of knowing, one which is based on' b'presuppositions. but if knowledge proceeds on what must be presupposed before' b'it is proved, the cover is blown on the pretentions of critical doubt, and' b'critical doubt depends on the idea that human knowledge is totally objective' b'and neutral. in other words, another myth.' b'' b'presuppositions my friend. it is impossible to doubt anything unless there is' b'something we do not doubt -our own assumptions/presuppostions. even these can' b'be criticezed only upon the basis of other assumptions. presuppostitons are' b'our silent partners in thought but their silence must not be mistaken for' b'absence.' b'' b' i tell you what-- if god condemns me for being honest, he is' b' unworthy of my worship. better to burn in hell than to' b' serve a tyrant in heaven..' b'' b'of course that is hardly an original statement. milton coined it but it had' b'been in use for millenia. it was even used in the first "highlander" movie.' b'but again, your presuption is based on a faulty knowledge of the character of' b'god. you are operating off of a presuppositional premise of humanistic' b'theology, not what he has revealed of himself through history, through his' b'prophets, through his word, and lastly, but most of all, thru his son. if you' b"are to reject god's annointed savior, then reject him from a correct" b'understanding of himself.' b'' b'--rex' 